news.title: Kanpur development body plots sold at more than their reserved price
news.para: The KDA in fact has auctioned 405 plots out of a total 480 plots whose estimated reserve price was Rs 76,95,34,809.00 and were sold at the cost of Rs. 152,73,95,406.00.

news.title: Ahmedabad fails to develop transit corridors: Study
news.para: However, unlike several Indian and international cities that have been developed around transit corridors, Ahmedabad has not been able to capitalize on these corridors, claimed the study.

news.title: Pune civic body to reissue tax bills of two lakh properties without discount
news.para: The process to finalise the new bill amounts for them is underway. It is expected to be completed by December-end, paving way for new bills’ issuance,” said Ajit Deshmukh, head of PMC’s property tax department.

news.title: ED registers case against Tulsiani Builders' CMD & MD for loan fraud
news.para: ED registered a case following a complaint lodged by the manager of Punjab National Bank who alleged that Tulsiani Group directors took a loan of Rs 4.63 crore after furnishing forged documents and did not respond to correspondence for recovery of loan amount.

news.title: No verification of tenants? Landlords in Ghaziabad to face action
news.para: The move follows the arrest of several criminals who were staying on rent without verification. Cosp also found out that many criminals were expelled from their districts like Noida, Bulandshahr and Meerut and have been residing in Ghaziabad without proper verification.

news.title: Sweden's SBB gathers residential assets in subsidiary ahead of share sale
news.para: SBB, which has racked up vast debt by buying public property, said in November it was looking for equity partners to help reduce its debt, as it tries to strengthen its financial stability and streamline operations.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers IPO subscribed 71% on first day of subscription
news.para: The portion for Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) got subscribed 1.23 times while the quota for non-institutional investors received 28 per cent subscription. The Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) part got subscribed 12 per cent.

news.title: Ambuja Cements to invest Rs 6,000 crore to produce 1,000 MW renewable power
news.para: The lineup includes a 600 MW Solar Power project and 150 MW wind power project in Gujarat and a 250 MW solar power project in Rajasthan

news.title: Housing sales value to cross Rs 4.5 lakh crore in 2023: Anarock
news.para: In the first nine months of 2023, the total residential property sales value in top seven cities touched approximately Rs 3,48,776 crore. Between January and September 2023, about 3.49 lakh units were sold in the top seven cities, according to the data by Anarock group.

news.title: NBCC sells 2.23 lakh sq ft of commercial space in Delhi for Rs 905 crore
news.para: As on date, NBCC has sold a total unsold commercial inventory of 23.92 lakh sq.ft. through open e-auction having sale value of Rs. 9,656.62 crore.

news.title: Aparna Enterprises to invest Rs 50 crore to expand its uPVC division in South-East Asian countries
news.para: Aparna Enterprises hopes that these new countries will contribute 20% to Ökotech’s total revenue in the future. Its foray into these markets is also expected to create 500 new job opportunities.

news.title: Power bill of 43% of homes using rooftop solar down by Rs 1,000: Study
news.para: The study - conducted jointly by MS University in Vadodara along with Gujarat Urja Vikas Nigam Limited (GUVNL) - assessed the socio-economic impact of solar rooftop scheme (Surya Gujarat) on residential consumers here.

news.title: Online system to make e-khata process simple in Mangaluru
news.para: "Khata will be distributed to applicants through the e-aasthi online software. Under the newly introduced online system, account registration and application for transfer of property khata can be made by citizens on their own through a few simple steps,” said MCC commissioner Anand CL.

news.title: Property tax on building only after completion of work: Karnataka HC
news.para: Allowing the petition filed by M/s BM Habitat, Justice Suraj Govindaraj directed Mysuru City Corporation to receive property tax vis-a-vis the petitioner’s multiplex building on Vinobhanagar Road, Jayalakshmipuram, from April 25, 2011, the date when the occupancy certificate came to be issued.

news.title: Mumbai: 13 years after offer to builder, Mhada lets CHS self-redevelop
news.para: Mhada, through its advocate P G Lad, has informed the HC that it has now issued an offer letter to the Chembur Nishant Cooperative Housing Society (CHS).

news.title: NAREDCO recommends SWAMIH 2.0, ITC under GST for residential projects ahead of budget FY25
news.para: In its letter to the finance minister, Nirmala Sitharaman, NAREDCO reiterated its long-standing request for allowing the option of claiming input tax credit by residential project developers with higher GST.

news.title: Gurugram: Structural audit of highrises stuck, builders yet to pay fee for second round
news.para: The district administration and the department of town and country planning (DTCP) have sent multiple reminders to developers over the past six months to deposit the fee, officials said on Sunday.

news.title: Post Adani takeover, ACC-Ambuja Cement's EBITDA rises to Rs 1,350 per tonne
news.para: Ambuja Cement has a cement capacity of 31 million tonne per annum with 6 integrated cement manufacturing plants and 8 cement grinding units across the country.

news.title: Noida authority's CEO meets builders, asks them to clear water dues
news.para: Officials from the water department were directed to make sure Sethi Buildwell Pvt Ltd cleared the dues, Rs 1.07 crore, in time.

news.title: SC upholds Palais Royale's 2019 sale to Pune's Honest Shelters
news.para: On December 6, the SC upheld its sale by Indiabulls Housing at a public auction in 2019 under the Sarfaesi Act to a little-known Pune developer, Honest Shelters, which paid Rs 705 crore for it.
